<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resolution on Withdrawal of Banknotes Issued </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Resolution on Withdrawal of Banknotes Issued </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005221194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2015 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005221194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- The Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine and 
National Bank of Ukraine [NBU] adopted a joint resolution on 28 
May "On the Withdrawal from Circulation of Coupons with a 
Nominal Value of 10 and 25 Karbovantsi." Proceeding from the 
inexpediency of further using these banknotes in cash settlement 
operations, the Cabinet of Ministers and the NBU have obliged 
regional boards of the NBU and commercial banks to ensure that 
the 10 and 25 karbovantsi banknotes are withdrawn from 
circulation by 1 August. Banknotes that have been withdrawn 
will be kept in regional NBU branches until the NBU decides on 
the issue of their recovery. The banknotes remain legal tender 
by all entities of entrepreneurial activity, regardless of their 
form of activity, by banks, and by enterprises of the Ministry 
of Communications until the time limit determined by the 
resolution. The resolution says that in connection with this, 
from 1 June the setting of retail prices for goods, services, 
and works should be carried out in figures that are a multiple 
of 50. 

</TEXT>

