<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Militia To Be Increased in Fight Against Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Militia To Be Increased in Fight Against Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805220794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2805220794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The numbers of operational purpose formations and 
military units of the internal forces of Russia's Internal 
Affairs Ministry will be increased by 52,000 units. This is 
provided for in the federal program for stepping up the fight 
against crime in 1994-1995, which has been sanctioned by the 
president. In accordance with the program, the rights of the 
militia will be expanded. It is proposed that it should be 
granted the right to inspect the buildings of enteprises and 
institutions, irrespective of the type of ownership, in cases 
where information is available that a crime is to be committed. 
The rules are to be changed regarding the use of weapons by law 
enforcement bodies staff during the fulfillment of their 
official duties. It is planned to set up special militia 
subunits to escort long-distance trains and suburban trains. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

