<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 27 May -- Russian Federation President Boris 
Yeltsin today issued a decree on changes to the Council for 
Personnel Policy under the Russian president. 
  According to the document, Nikolay Yegorov is replacing 
Sergey Shakhray on the Council. This follows the president's 
edict of 16 May relating to the minister for affairs of 
nationalities and regional policy, the president's press service 
said. 

