<H3> <TI>   Russian TV Head on Duma Radio, TV Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian TV Head on Duma Radio, TV Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705165494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1354 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 27 TASS -- The Russian State Duma has 
proved to be adherent to the former Supreme Soviet's traditions, 
Chairman of the All-Russian TV and Radio Company Oleg Poptsov 
told ITAR-TASS here today, commenting on the Duma decision to 
form its own TV and radio service. 
  In his opinion, the Duma "claims on certain information 
exclusiveness", which may provoke a chain reaction on the part 
of other power structures, including the juridical one. "Then 
we will have a splendid TV and the radio," said Poptsov. 
  Lamenting there were no deputies to show wisdom and 
understanding, Poptsov stressed "the main feature of democracy 
is openness, modesty and availability of power bodies, their 
ability of self-estimation, and not claims on privileges". 

</TEXT>

