in the Krasnodar region, southern Russia, on Saturday, Gaydar 
said that the major problem is that the government's economic 
programme offers little hope for the future. 
  He stressed that the government's course provides for the 
preservation of the status quo which excludes any prospects for 
economic growth. 
  Gaydar presented the delegates with a 33-page programme of 
the Russia's Choice bloc. 

