<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Calls For 11 Key Social, Economic Programs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Calls For 11 Key Social, Economic Programs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005193294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1844 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Boris Yeltsin has given instructions to 
develop 11 important social and economic programs. In addition 
the government is preparing some 20 programs to resolve several 
key problems in industry. This was reported to Interfax by the 
head of the presidential staff Sergey Filatov. 
  According to him, presidential programs concern primarily 
health and environmental protection. The medical industry must 
be promoted, in particular the production of insulin and protein 
for the food industry. Another program provides for the 
transition to energy-consuming technologies in different 
branches of the economy, including the auto industry. 
  Filatov stressed that the implementation of this important 
program will give a new impetus to Russian engineering. He said 
things have gone to a point when Russian vehicles are not 
permitted to Europe because they do not meet international 
environmental safety norms. 
  Filatov also hopes that the planned reduction of the 
consumption of gasoline and gas will considerably improve 
transport energy supplies. 
  A public telephone program, Filatov said, will help 
radically 
improve communications in rural areas as well as cities. Some 
of the new programs provide for the development of natural 
resources, in particular new deposits in Tyumen and the Barents 
sea, the expansion of the transport network and others. 

</TEXT>

