<H3> <TI>   Shokhin Explains Yeltsin's Economic Reform Edicts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shokhin Explains Yeltsin's Economic Reform Edicts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105143494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1354 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 31 TASS -- The recent package of 
presidential economic decrees was caused by the government's 
inability to achieve the quick adoption of economic bills at the 
State Duma, Russian Vice-Premier and Minister of Economy 
Aleksandr Shokhin told a news conference here today. 
  The government had to ask the president to approve measures 
necessary for further economic reforms by his decrees, said 
Shokhin. 
  "We plan to use presidential decrees and government 
resolutions for swift reaction to Russian economic processes," 
stressed the vice-premier. "Another package of presidential 
decrees will soon be signed". The package will include the 
prepared draft presidential decrees on sales of 
enterprises-debtors and regulation of the consumption fund of 
enterprises, as well as the decrees under elaboration on legal 
basis of foreign economic activities (to eliminate personal 
benefits in this sphere) and regulation of banking activities. 
  The president is ready for joint and quick solution of major 
economic problems, stressed Shokhin. 

</TEXT>

