<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Offers Economic Recovery Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Offers Economic Recovery Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK3105100594 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 31 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK3105100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["I.R." report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Glazyev on the </F>
Economic Situation"] 
  [Text] Speaking in his yesterday's press conference, 
Sergey Glazyev, Duma Economic Policy Committee chairman, stated 
that his own prognoses and those of his colleagues made in March 
have been confirmed by the findings of the Economic Conditions 
Center under the Russian Federation Government: The production 
slump in 1994 will be around 25 percent, that is to say, it will 
become "precipitous." Besides, "there are no special signs of 
recovery in sight that could indicate that this is a turning 
point," Mr. Glazyev stressed. He presented "State's Economic 
Policy Guidelines" developed by a group of economists. Their 
main idea is to bring order into all the sectors of the economy 
and in the system of its control, for which purpose specific 
measures are proposed. Remarkably, in the expression of Mr. 
Glazyev himself, measures which can indeed be implemented have 
been specially selected from a multitude of suggestions. 

</TEXT>

