<H3> <TI>   Russia Fixes Limit for Foreign Loans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Fixes Limit for Foreign Loans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105101694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0949 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 31 TASS -- The upper chamber of the 
Russian parliament approved a federal law on Tuesday fixing the 
limit for foreign loans at 4.7 billion us dollars this year. 
The limit for Russian state credits to other countries has been 
set at 400 million dollars in 1994. 
  Chairman of the Finance and Budget Committee of the 
Federation Council Nikolay Gonchar commented that the law is 
aimed to avert a further increase of the Russian foreign debt 
which exceeded 80 billion dollars by the beginning of 1994. 

</TEXT>

