<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Pledges No Social Cutbacks for Servicemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Pledges No Social Cutbacks for Servicemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705141794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1318 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 27 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin addressed a meeting held in Moscow on the occasion of 
the day of border guards, expressing a principal position on 
problems of social welfare of servicemen and their families. 
Yeltsin pointed out that as the Russian president, he will not 
allow any social or legal cuts for people wearing shoulder 
straps. Yeltsin pointed out that social problems faced by 
servicemen are the result of the economic situation in the 
country. 
  The Russian president heartily congratulated border guards 
on 
the occasion of the day of border guards, he pointed out that 
over the past 1.5 years, the title of the Hero of the Russian 
Federation was conferred upon six border guards, and over 400 
border guards were awarded with medals and orders. 
  During the meeting a minute of silence was observed in 
memory 
of border guards who were killed defending Russian borders. 

</TEXT>

