<H3> <TI>   TM-19 Spacecraft Launch Postponed to Late Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TM-19 Spacecraft Launch Postponed to Late Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705170994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 
27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] The launch of the next Mir 
crew has been postponed, as Colonel General Vladimir Ivanov, 
commander of Russia's Military Space Forces, has confirmed. 
According to unofficial information, the launch has had to be 
postponed because of a hold-up in testing the nose fairing on 
the Soyuz spacecraft: The fairing covers the craft during the 
launch when the rocket is going through the Earth's atmosphere. 
TM-19 was initially due to blast off on 20 June; now the 
possibilities of carrying out a launch on the 29 or 31 June are 
being examined. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

