<H3> <TI>   Abkhazian Forces Regain Positions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhazian Forces Regain Positions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705180094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1508 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705180094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] By the evening of May 26 the Abkhazian formations 
had won back their positions in the Kodor Gorge (Abkhazia) lost 
in the morning when the Georgian troops launched an attack. 
Sukhumi reported that the Georgian troops had succeeded in 
breaking through by about 300 meters near the village of 
Verkhnya Lata. 
  A representative of the Abkhazian Defense Ministry told 
Interfax that the Georgian units had suffered significant losses 
and had retreated. He did not mention Abkhaz losses. 
  The night of May 26-7 and following morning were relatively 
calm in the Kodor Gorge. 
  The Georgian Defense Ministry has denied attacking the Kodor 
Gorge. 

</TEXT>

