<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Georgians Continue Shelling Kodor Gorge </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Georgians Continue Shelling Kodor Gorge </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105095994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0935 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 31 TASS -- Georgian forces which have 
occupied positions above the village of Lata in the Kodor Gorge 
fired over 100 howitzer shells on local Abkhazian settlements 
over three days, TASS was told by the press service of the 
Abkhazian parliament on Tuesday. 
  Georgian units tried to drive Abkhazians out of their 
positions overnight, but were repelled, it added. 
  The village of Lata again became the strategic point for 
which the conflicting sides are fighting. The Georgian forces 
which were pushed up into the mountains want to seize it for a 
further offensive down into Abkhazia. Abkhazians, naturally, 
are defending the stronghold. 
  Military experts predict that combat activities will 
intensify in the gorge soon as the important location provides 
an access to the Black Sea. The forecasts are proved by several 
days of artillery preparations by Georgian forces. 

</TEXT>

