  [Text] Baku, May 27 (TURAN) -- According to Azerbaijan 
Defense Ministry, relative calm on the front line was broken 
yesterday night. 
  Beginning from May 26 at 20.30 p.m. Azeri positions near 
Akhmedagali (Agdamskiy region) were shelled. 
  During night on May 27 Armenian troops shelled the village 
Sadarak (Nakhichevan Republic). In both cases Azeri side did 
not open fire. 
  TURAN was told by the informed sources from Azeri Defence 
Ministry that shelling of Azeri positions was not by chance; the 
order came from Yerevan. The same source told that in spite of 
the fact of reconciliation, Armenian commandment continue to 
gather its technical and live forces in the North of Karabakh. 

