<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Acceptance of Draft Economic Program Delayed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Acceptance of Draft Economic Program Delayed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2905195094 Yerevan SNARK in English 0516 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2905195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Business SNARK" file] </F>
  [Text] BAKU [dateline as received] -- The economic program 
draft acceptance by the Ministers' Cabinet of Azerbaijan is 
delayed, told the Economy Ministry official. The draft project 
was submitted to the Ministers' Cabinet in March. 
  Authors of the program claim that the draft is drawn by the 
private initiative, not by the order of government, and is based 
on scenario of government activity, with specific targets and 
roles of economic institutions. Before submission, the draft 
was agreed with all these institutions. Project includes the 
acceptance of 87 laws and sub-law acts providing the necessary 
conditions for normal functioning of economy. 
  To this instant, told the authors, the project has been cut 
almost for a half and divided into several units. "This 
violates the project integrity and makes the program 
impractical". 

</TEXT>

