<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur Rules out Intervention in Ukraine </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur Rules out Intervention in Ukraine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705162994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1135 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] May 27 TASS -- "The situation 
in Ukraine is an internal affair of that country and does not 
require outside intervention," Moldavian [Moldovan] President 
Mircea Snegur said today. "Any advice and instruction might 
result in grave consequences. Ukraine, according to its 
Constitution, is an integral state, and we hope that it will 
resolve the problems, which have cropped up through peaceful 
negotiations. We are not indifferent to how the situation 
develops in our neighbouring state with whom we maintain cordial 
relations," the Moldavian head of state said. 
  According to Mircea Snegur, the events in Ukraine belong to 
the category of those which are caused by seperatism. 
Seperatist tendencies should be condemned, since they do not 
lead to anything good. Conflicting situations in the former 
Soviet Union and in the whole world testify to this fact. I 
condemn seperatism as a phenomenon," the Moldavian leader 
emphasised. 
  The Moldavian president expressed the hope that forces 
capable of regulating problems in the Crimea would be found. 
According to him, these problems "are a result of the 
populistic activities of certain politicians, who are 
unwarrantedly claiming too much." 

</TEXT>

