<H3> <TI>   Government-Opposition Tehran Talks Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government-Opposition Tehran Talks Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105101494 Tehran IRNA in English 1000 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dushanbe, May 31, IRNA -- A Tajik Foreign Ministry 
official here Tuesday said that the talks between Tajik 
Government and the opposition leaders, due to be held in Tehran 
on June 4, has been postponed. 
  The official, wishing to remain anonymous, also said that no 
exact date has so far been fixed for the new round of talks 
between the two sides. However, it may be held in Tehran on 
June 17, he added. 
  Both the Tajik authorities and the opposition leaders had 
agreed to begin talks on June 4. However, the date has changed 
after the recent visit to Tajikistan of a United Nations envoy. 
  In another develpoment, Iran Red Crescent Society has sent 
some 11 tons of humanitarian aids including food, medicine and 
clothing to victims of war in Tajikistan. 

