<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finnish President Arrives, Talks With President Meri </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105100694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 0900 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari began his 
two-day state visit to Estonia, when his aircraft landed at 
Tallinn airport two hours ago. At 1100 an official welcoming 
ceremony took place at Kadriorg presidential residence, attended 
by Estonian President Lennart Meri, Premier Mart Laar, and 
Ambassador to Finland Jaak Joeruut. The Finnish president is 
accompanied by Foreign Minister Heikki Haavisto and Finnish 
Ambassador to Estonia Jaakko Kaurinkoski. 
  After the ceremony Martti Ahtisaari and Lennart Meri held 
talks. They discussed Estonian-Finnish relations and European 
Union membership. No particular attention will be paid to 
Estonian- Russian relations during Martti Ahtisaari's visit. 
[passage omitted] 

