<H3> <TI>   Main Staff of CIS Armed Forces Said Superseded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Main Staff of CIS Armed Forces Said Superseded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0106074094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 1 Jun 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0106074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Hold The Front Page!" </F>
rubric: "CIS Troops Brought Into Moscow"] 
  [Text] It has come to MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS's attention 
that the Main Staff of the CIS Joint Forces has finally ceased 
to exist. 
  It has been transformed into a staff for coordination in the 
area of military cooperation. Out of the 480 officers, 360 have 
retired. The remaining 120 Russian staff officers will be 
supplemented by 120 officers from the CIS-states' armed forces. 
  Russian military men who have gone through the General Staff 
school are not forming a high opinion about the newly arriving 
officers. At the moment the staff for coordination of military 
cooperation has begun to fulfill its first mission -- to form 
the military part of a concept of military security of... Russia. 

</TEXT>

