<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yavlinskiy Doubts `Realism' of Economic Edicts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yavlinskiy Doubts `Realism' of Economic Edicts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK3105123094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 31 May 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK3105123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- Grigoriy Yavlinskiy, leader of the 
"Yabloko" faction in the State Duma, doubts that Boris Yeltsin's 
recent economic edicts are going to "work." He has pointed out 
that on the whole, the direction of movement on the road of 
economic reform chosen by this package of documents is correct, 
but the "very execution of the edicts leaves much to be 
desired." "Politically, this is an attempt by the president to 
seize the initiative in the absence of such in the government. 
However, the content of the edicts raises big doubts as to the 
realism of the measures implied by them," G. Yavlinskiy stressed. 

</TEXT>

