<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Breaches Law Over Airbus Imports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Breaches Law Over Airbus Imports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005213794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1736 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005213794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] When he signed a government ordinance making A-310 
aircraft and their parts exempt from customs duties, Viktor 
Chernomyrdin was in breach of the Russian law because the 
government has no right to make such decisions, Sergey Glazyev, 
chairman of the State Duma Economic Policy Committee, told 
INTERFAX Monday. 
  A-310-300 planes are imported into Russia by Aeroflot under 
a 
leasing agreement with a consortium of European banks. Four air 
buses of this kind are now in operation in Russia. A fifth 
crashed near Mezhdurechensk, a town in the Kemerovo Region, 
killing 75 passengers and crew. 
  Glazyev believed that the losses incurred in operating the 
A-310's was the sole reason why Aeroflot was given tax relief. 
  Without this relief, the new import duties to be imposed as 
of July 1 on aircraft and their parts would kill the idea of 
importing A-310's, Glazyev believed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38497 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov105_b_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-105 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Mayor Rejects Chubays-Style Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Mayor Rejects Chubays-Style Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105170894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1613 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Leonid Galinskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 31 TASS -- "There will be no 
privatization a la Chubays in Moscow," Moscow Mayor Yuriy 
Luzhkov told ITAR-TASS here today. "It is not the matter of 
conflict between the chairman of the State Committee for 
Property and me, but essential differences in the vitally 
important issue of the implementation of the state privatization 
program". 
  Commenting on the recent appeal of Anatoliy Chubays to the 
Russian procurator general's office in connection with the 
Moscow mayor's privatization resolutions, Luzhkov said "I accept 
this proposal of Mr Chubays with readiness, but I want him to 
visit the procurator general's office together with me. I am 
convinced that it is not my privatization resolutions that run 
counter to the law but resolutions of the State Property 
Committee". 
  In the opinion of Luzhkov, "the state institution has 
usurped 
the right to solve all problems in privatization and sometimes 
makes serious mistakes" . 
  "We think that property should be sold and not squandered or 
given away dirt cheap to anyone. That is why, I believe that 
voucher privatization is a swindle to be investigated by the 
procurator general due to the inadmissibility to squander state 
property," he stressed. 
  Asked about major drawbacks in privatization, Luzhkov said 
"I 
am sure that privatization a la Chubays has brought almost no 
positive results. It brought us no additional property. It 
only ruins the state. Russia gained no new owners and 
proprietors, as Chubays has promised. Privatization resulted in 
an enormous number of speculators who are looking for an 
opportunity to sell at high prices what they have bought dirt 
cheap". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38498 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov105_b_94010" </HT>


