<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice Premier Anticipates Large-Scale Unemployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Premier Anticipates Large-Scale Unemployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105140194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1327 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lilya Kuznetsova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 31 TASS -- Large-scale unemployment is 
fraught with such a social explosion that consequences of 
hyper-inflation will seem a trifle, Russian Vice-Premier Yuriy 
Yarov told a seminar-conference on social development of Russian 
regions here today. 
  In his words, the situation will run out of control in the 
near future if the government, the federal employment service 
and the local authorities take no immediate measures to prevent 
large-scale unemployment. 
  According to forecasts of specialists, the number of 
officially registered unemployed will reach three millions by 
the end of this year. The concealed unemployment that is 
currently estimated at approximately seven million will at least 
double. 
  Unemployment has turned into a major problem of social 
services. It should be settled by joint efforts of the 
authorities, employment centers and trade unions, said Yarov. 
  In his opinion, the state should allocate money for payment 
of dole from the federal budget to those regions and districts 
that are in critical condition. The state debt of regions with 
a high rate of unemployment should be paid fully and in the 
first turn. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

