<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Budget Deficit Reaches 11 Percent of GNP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Budget Deficit Reaches 11 Percent of GNP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005213094 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1920 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Mutual non-payments remain a characteristic feature 
of the Russian economy. This has been confirmed by the latest 
figures from the State Statistics Committee. As of 1 April 1994 
the total debt of industrial enterprises, construction 
businesses, transport and agriculture amounted to 93 trillion 
rubles. 
  According to the estimates of the economics institute for 
the 
problems of the transition period, the budget deficit for the 
first quarter has already reached 11 percent of the Gross 
National Product. Let me remind you that in its draft budget 
for 1994, the government undertook not to exceed the 10 percent 
mark for its deficit. 
  There are still budgetary debts to a number of industries. 
This in turn leads to non-payments on the part of the 
enterprises, not only to each other and to banks, but to the 
budget as well. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

