<H3> <TI>   State Duma Chairman Receives Kuwaiti Counterpart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Chairman Receives Kuwaiti Counterpart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005123494 Moscow RIA in English 1038 GMT 30 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3005123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 30, RIA -- "Russia insists on an 
unconditional fulfilment in full volume of all resolutions of 
the UN Security Council with respect to Iraq", said the chairman 
of the State Duma, Ivan Rybkin, in the course of his meeting 
today with the chairman of the National Assembly of Kuwait, 
Ahmad 'Abd-al-'Aziz al- Sa'dun who is on an official visit to 
Russia. 
  "The position of Russia is immutable since 1990 when Iraq 
started its aggression against Kuwait", Ivan Rybkin pointed out. 
For his own part, the chairman of the Kuwait parliament 
expressed gratitude for Russia's actions in the UN Security 
Council and the hope that they would continue to contribute to 
the final settlement of the problem. According to the chairman 
of the Kuwait National Assembly, "peace in the region can only 
be established after a final demarcation of the border between 
Kuwait and Iraq and the completion of the exchange of prisoners". 

</TEXT>

