<H3> <TI>   Agrarian Faction Criticizes State Secretary's Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agrarian Faction Criticizes State Secretary's Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005213994 Moscow RIA in English 1700 GMT 30 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3005213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 30, RIA--The Duma faction of the 
Agrarian Party of Russia considers as "political indecency" the 
far from proper word used by former Russian Secretary of State 
Gennadiy Burbulis in the Sunday Itogi television programme to 
describe the way the new Constitution of Russia was adopted. 
  This is said in a statement issued by the faction. The 
faction believes that Burbulis insulted millions of people who 
on December 12 voted for the new fundamental law. 
  "The Agrarian Party was firmly against the adopted version 
of 
the Constitution. Mr Burbulis must have forgotten the vigour 
and persistence with which the presidential team, in which Mr 
Burbulis had no last role to play, was pushing through its draft 
of the fundamental law," said the statement. 
  The document also mentions "Mr Burbulis's sinister role in 
the history of Russia of the recent period". 

</TEXT>

