<H3> <TI>   Tanker With Radioactive Waste Towed to Safe Place </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tanker With Radioactive Waste Towed to Safe Place </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005113694 Moscow RIA in English 0756 GMT 30 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3005113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladivostok, May 30, RIA -- A TNT-5 tanker with 
liquid radioactive wastes has been tugged to far roads in the 
Pavlovskiy harbour from the wharves of the "Zvezda" plant in the 
city of Bolshoy Kamen. The operation to move the vessel to a 
safe place was ordered by the Pacific Fleet command after the 
workers of the plant and the mass media spread concern over a 
possible spill of radioactive wastes into the sea. Even though 
after a careful inspection of the vessel specialists did not 
register any increased radioactivity or the penetration of sea 
water into the containers with wastes, it was decided to take 
the tanker away from the shore. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

