<H3> <TI>   N. Ossetia Administration Head on Law Violations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    N. Ossetia Administration Head on Law Violations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005164394 Moscow RIA in English 1254 GMT 20 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2005164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladikavkaz, May 20 (RIA) -- In connection with the 
seizure of five Ingush citizens in a suburb of Vladikavkaz last 
night, Vladimir Lozovoi, head of the provisional administration 
on part of the territories of Northern Ossetia and Ingushetia in 
the rank of vice-premier, has issued an official statement for 
the mass media. The statement notes, in particular, that "of 
late gross violations of law and order, explosions of military 
equipment, shellings of the Russian Army's peace-making forces 
and seizures of hostages have become more frequent in the area 
of the emergency situation." Lozovoi has called upon the 
relatives and friends of the captured men to remain calm and 
restrained and assured them that all necessary steps would be 
taken for their release. 
  The head of the provisional administration stressed that the 
appropriate measures would be taken with regard to the 
authorities and heads of law-enforcement bodies of Northern 
Ossetia and Ingushetia who are unable or unwilling to carry out 
their duties in introducing law and order. The inactivity of 
the authorities of both republics may lead to an aggravation of 
the situation in the entire south of Russia, the statement 
notes. 

</TEXT>

