<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Deputies Meet With Estonian Colleagues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Deputies Meet With Estonian Colleagues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505180694 Moscow RIA in English 1528 GMT 25 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2505180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, May 25, RIA -- Today, our choice and revel 
factions of the Tallinn City Assembly met with Konstantin 
Zatulin, chairman of Russia's State Duma Committee on 
Commonwealth Affairs and Liaison with fellow-citizens, and 
Vladislav Tumanov, deputy of the Council of the Federation. 
  Speaking of the problem of Russians in Estonia, Zatulin said 
that "it is very important to us to see that human rights are 
observed not only in South Africa but in Estonia as well." 
  Tumanov said it was wrong of Estonia to allege that 7,000 
Estonian citizens reside in Russia's Pechora district. 
According to him, it has been established that there is one 
hundred Estonians residing there. Tumanov believes that the 
Pechora district with a population of 30,000 is Russian from 
time immemorial and must remain part of Russia, no matter how 
the government of Estonia may treat this. In his view, the 
conclusion of an Estonian-Russian Treaty on Contiguous Areas is 
the first step towards resolving controversies. 

</TEXT>

