<H3> <TI>   Last Russian Naval Ship To Leave 1 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Last Russian Naval Ship To Leave 1 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105120994 Moscow RIA in English 1029 GMT 31 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3105120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, May 31, RIA -- In accordance with the 
bilateral agreements signed on April 30 in Moscow, tomorrow, on 
June 1, the three last Russian naval ships will leave Liepaja 
[Latvia]. 
  As the spokesman of the Latvian Defence Ministry has 
declared, the Latvian side, in taking over the facilities of the 
Russian navy, is encountering certain difficulties. In 
particular, they are connected with their further utilisation, 
as well as the need to free the water area of the former Liepaja 
military port and other former Russian naval bases from the 
several dozen ships and submarines sunk there. 

</TEXT>

