<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Presidential Candidates Registered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Presidential Candidates Registered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0106081094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 1 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK0106081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Valentin Zhdanko report from Minsk: "Vyacheslav Kebich Has </F>
Lost His Main Rival"] 
  [Text] On 31 May the Central Election Commission 
registered the following as Belorussia's [Belarus] official 
presidential candidates: Premier Vyacheslaw Kebich, ex-speaker 
Stanislaw Shushkevich, Belorussian National Front leader Zenon 
Poznyak, deputy Aleksandr Lukashenko, Communist Party leader 
Vasiliy Novikov, and kolkhoz chairman Aleksandr Dubko. 
  Gennadiy Karpenko, leader of the Party of National Accord, 
who was considered one of Kebich's main contenders in the 
elections, did not make it into the candidates' list. Karpenko 
had polled the required number of signatures but at the last 
moment 16 deputies unexpectedly recalled their signatures. 
Yesterday, without waiting for a Central Election Commission 
decision, Gennadiy Karpenko withdrew his candidacy. 

</TEXT>

