<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chechen Opposition Rejects Terrorism for Political Aims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chechen Opposition Rejects Terrorism for Political Aims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105203894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1917 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105203894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In its statement today the Chechen opposition 
categorically rejects terrorism as a way of achieving political 
aims and urged the Chechen people to remain calm and not to 
react to similar provocations. The statement was circulated 
following the recent assassination attempt against Chechen 
President Dzhokhar Dudayev. 
  In Chechnya any terrorist act may trigger off civil war with 
unpredictable consequences, the statement underlined. 
  The opposition described the assassination attempt as a 
result of the criminal policy of the Chechen leadership from the 
very beginning aimed at linking up with criminal structures. 
  This proves that the leadership can exercise no real 
influence on the situation which encourages different armed 
groups seeking power. As a rule, such groups have no social 
support and resort to terrorism, the statement said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

