<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Views Relations With Tatarstan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Views Relations With Tatarstan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105160894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1400 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report from Kazan by correspondent Andrey Murtazin, </F>
including recording of remarks made to journalists by President 
Boris Yeltsin; from the "Novosti" newscast] 
  [Excerpt] [Murtazin] [passage omitted] Replying to 
questions from journalists, Boris Yeltsin noted that treaty 
relations between the Tatarstan and the center are being 
implemented. True, since the beginning of the year Kazan has 
incurred a debt of 43 billion rubles, but this is mainly because 
of mutual non-payments between enterprises. 
  [Yeltsin] We are living in accordance with the treaty. You 
understand? In the treaty we have divided up the functions 
between the state powers of Tatarstan and the Russian 
Federation. Each has undertaken certain functions which it is 
performing and for which it must be responsible, and for which 
it must receive money. So sources are obtained from here and 
from there. So it cannot be called subsidies. It is simply the 
correct distribution of labor and finance. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

