GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 31 May -- Russian Federation President Boris 
Yeltsin has just returned to Moscow from Kazan. He spent two 
days on a working visit to Tatarstan. Druing the trip, he 
visited Naberezhnyye Chelny, where he familiarized himself with 
the problems of the KAMAZ motor vehicle works. 
  The main point of today's meeting with the leadership of the 
republic in the capital of Tatarstan was to work out the 
machinery for the implementation of Russia's treaty with 
Tatarstan. The president of Russia and his counterpart Mintimer 
Shaymiyev confirmed this to journalists at the end of their 
meeting in the Kazan Kremlin. 

