<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Mayor Accused of Privatization Irregularity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Mayor Accused of Privatization Irregularity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705172994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1516 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 27 TASS -- A representation to cancel the 
regulations on privatization in Moscow, which were prepared on 
the instruction of Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov and run counter to 
the current legislation, has been made by Chairman of the 
Russian State Property Committee Anatoliy Chubays to the Russian 
procurator general's office. 
  "Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov has launched a campaign of 
large-scale violations of privatization legislation and even 
fully prohibited the transfer of state property into private in 
the city," Chubays told correspondents. 
  In his words, the Moscow City Committee for Property 
gradually stopped corporatization and sales of Moscow 
enterprises at privatization voucher auctions. The share of 
joint stock enterprises in Moscow amounted to 15 per cent from 
the overall number of enterprises liable for corporatization in 
April 1994, as compared to 62 per cent throughout Russia. 
Moscow is lagging behind in privatization of large enterprises 
as well. 
  The privatization situation in Moscow can be estimated as 
catastrophic, said Chubays. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

