<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Criticizes Implementation of Economic Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Criticizes Implementation of Economic Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105162294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [text] The Cabinet of Ministers Presidium session today 
discussed issues which are important for the reform of our 
country's economy. In particular, the course of implementation 
of the governments measures to promote economic policy this 
year, the concept and program of measures aimed at 
demonopolizing the national economy were discussed. A heated 
exchange of opinions took place on what is hindering the 
resolution of these problems. The lack of flexibility among 
heads of ministries and departments as well as of the government 
apparatus was criticized. 
  It was stressed that in view of the serious state of the 
country's economic and social sphere it is no longer possible to 
tolerate such low executive discipline. Draft resolutions on 
the issues under discussion were returned for elaboration. 
Deadlines were fixed for this elaboration. The authors were 
told to display the highest level of professionalism during the 
preparation of the documents and to eliminate mistakes made in 
the drafts. 
  The Cabinet of Ministers Presidium also examined the 
implementation of intergovernmental agreements on transport and 
communications with neighboring southern countries. 
  The sitting was chaired by Prime Minister Sergey 
Tereshchenko. 

</TEXT>

