<F P=106> [Unattributed report] </F>
  [Text] In the evening of 23 May, Supreme Council Chairman 
Oleksandr Moroz received Israel's Ambassador Extraordinary and 
Plenipotentiary in Ukraine, Tzvi Magen, at the latter's request. 
In the course of the conversation, which proceeded in a 
businesslike and relaxed atmosphere, an exchange of opinions on 
the present socioeconomic and political situation in Ukraine 
took place, as well as on Ukrainian-Israeli relations and ways 
of developing them. Particular attention was given to questions 
of mutually advantageous cooperation between the two states and 
to prospects and directions for intensifying them. 

