<H3> <TI>   Talks on Fleet To Continue After Parliament Discussion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks on Fleet To Continue After Parliament Discussion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105162194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1335 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Moscow-Kiev talks on sharing out the Black Sea 
Fleet [BSF] will be continued after the Ukrainian parliament has 
discussed the issue, Ukrainian Vice Premier Valeriy Shmarov told 
Interfax-Ukraine on Tuesday. He said Kiev would use the 
deputies' position as a guideline in talks with Moscow. 
  Shmarov who was involved in last week's talks in Moscow on 
the future of the fleet said that examination was now under way 
of BSF's infrastructure in Crimea before the resumption of high 
level talks a bit later. 
  He invited the Russian delegation to Kiev describing it as a 
better venue for the second round of talks. 
  In the meantime, Russia's Deputy Defence Minister Boris 
Gromov and Special Envoy Yuriy Dubinin are due to arrive in Kiev 
on Tuesday, according to Interfax-Ukraine. 

