<H3> <TI>   Navy Stops Supplying Information to Black Sea Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy Stops Supplying Information to Black Sea Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105125594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1149 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Command of Ukraine's navy has stopped supplying 
the navigation services of the Black Sea Fleet with technical 
information. As a high-ranking official from the Naval Staff 
told INTERFAX-UKRAINA, this decision was taken because "the 
Black Sea Fleet Command refuses to resolve the issue of jointly 
ensuring the safety of navigation, including exchanges in 
navigation information." 
  Meanwhile, as the spokesman for Ukraine's navy said, the 
Odessa and Nikolayev hydrographic districts run by Kiev 
"regularly give information to Ukrainian and Russian civilian 
ships and to the Black Sea Fleet." "In the meantime, the Black 
Sea Fleet Command has failed to notify us even of the 
hydrographic works to be conducted in the Azov Sea in June, 
though such works must be coordinated officially," said 
INTERFAX-UKRAINA's interviewee. 

</TEXT>

