<H3> <TI>   Possible Introduction of Presidential Rule Mooted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Possible Introduction of Presidential Rule Mooted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105200494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1840 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani leadership is discussing the 
possible introduction of presidential rule in the republic and 
dismissal of the parliament, a high-ranking official close to 
the office of Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev told INTERFAX. 
He asked to remain anonymous. The source did not mention 
details. 
  Acting Chief of the president's Press Service Salahaddin 
Guliyev said in an interview with INTERFAX that the parliament 
would not be dismissed in the near future. Neither would 
presidential rule or other emergency measures be introduced. 
  Observers in Baku stressed that the Azerbaijani media had 
recently repeatedly mentioned appeals on the part of refugees 
demanding the dismissal of the parliament and to declaration of 
presidential rule. 

</TEXT>

