<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aide Urges Removal of People's Front From Parliament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aide Urges Removal of People's Front From Parliament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105205894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1926 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijani State Aide Arif Ragimzade proposed that 
high-ranking members of the opposition People's Front be removed 
from the parliament. This concerned former foreign minister 
Tofik Gasymov and First Deputy Chairman of the People's Front 
Ibrahim Ibrahimov. 
  Ragimzade proposed it this morning when the parliament was 
discussing the social-political situation in Azerbaijan on the 
initiative of Speaker Rasul Guliyev. The situation in 
Azerbaijan has become more tense due to the opposition 
protesting the position of the authorities on the settlement in 
Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  Azerbaijani Interior Minister Ramil Usubov laid the 
responsibility for the situation at the door of leader of the 
National Independence opposition party Etibar Mamedov. 
  In his turn, Mamedov blamed Usubov for misinformation of the 
Azerbaijani leadership and for actions of the police which, in 
his mind, were undermining stability in the country. 
  Former foreign minister Gasymov said that Speaker Guliyev 
was 
triggering off the tension since Guliyev had refused to discuss 
the Bishkek protocol on settlement in Karabakh in the 
parliament. This made the opposition take action. 

</TEXT>

