<H3> <TI>   National-Democratic Party Tops Party Popularity Poll </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National-Democratic Party Tops Party Popularity Poll </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005204994 Tbilisi AKHALI TAOBA in Georgian 20 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU3005204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi AKHALI TAOBA </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report on the results of an opinion poll: </F>
"The Population's Sympathies Lie With the Opposition"] 
  [Text] At the beginning of May, a sociological survey was 
carried out with the aim of establishing the popularity rating 
of political parties. The following political organizations 
topped the poll: The National-Democratic Party, the Republican 
Party, and the Popular Front. It is significant that the Union 
of [Georgia's] Citizens that was widely publicized by the 
authorities and that is led by the present head of state was 
only in ninth place. 
  As can be seen, the population's sympathies basically lean 
toward the opposition. This is also shown by the fact that 
eight of the 10 leading political organizations belong to the 
opposition. This shows once more that society is expecting 
significant changes in the government. 


