<H3> <TI>   Crimean Official on Threat of Nationalist Gunmen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Official on Threat of Nationalist Gunmen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1823 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol May 31 TASS -- Crimean president's aide 
Aleksey Baksheyev does not exclude the possibility that gunmen 
of the so-called Organization of Ukrainian Nationalists (OUN) 
are already penetrating the peninsula. 
  "Their threats to form special units for the Crimea are 
real", the aide told TASS on Tuesday. 
  According to Baksheyev, neither Ukrainians nor residents of 
the Crimean Republic are interested in aggravating tensions 
around the peninsula. People who benefit from these tensions 
are not numerous but they "stir up trouble immensely", he added. 
  "Kiev has nothing to wory about", he went on saying. "The 
Crimea does not look for separation, it just wants to build 
relations with Ukraine on a treaty basis". 
  On the contrary, the situation will be destabilized if 
President Kravchuk imposes his direct rule on Crimea, Baksheyev 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

