<H3> <TI>   350 Ukrainian Guards Moved to Sevastopol in May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    350 Ukrainian Guards Moved to Sevastopol in May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1315 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 31 TASS -- A total of 350 guards of a 
separate battalion of the Ukrainian national guards were shifted 
to Sevastopol between May 17 and 27. The battalion with 
motorised equipment is stationed on the grounds of an air 
defence unit of the Ukrainian Defence Ministry, the public 
relations centre of the Sevastopol Militia Department reports on 
Tuesday. 
  The report notes that Lieutenant-Colonel Igor Kurovskyy, 
commander of the guards unit stationed in Sevastopol, said that 
a decision on deploying such subunits in all the Ukrainian 
regional centres was taken by President Leonid Kravchuk in 1993. 
  He noted that the main tasks of guardsmen are to protect the 
Ukrainian constitutional system and to help border troops in 
detaining border transgressors. 
  In the near future, guardsmen intend to participate in 
measures to protect law and order, which were planned by the 
Sevastopol Militia Department. 

</TEXT>

