<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean `Shadow' Parliament's Appeal to Kiev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean `Shadow' Parliament's Appeal to Kiev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105213294 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A totalitarian dictatorship is emerging in Crimea, 
built on the basis of open Russian chauvinism. The 
newly-elected Supreme Council of Crimea and the autonomous 
republic's president, Yuriy Meshkov, have embarked on an 
unmasked course towards Crimea's separation from Ukraine. Thus 
states an appeal to the president and Supreme Council of Ukraine 
by Crimea's shadow parliament, the Civic Congress of Crimea, 
formed to consolidate progressive pro-Ukrainian democratic 
forces on the peninsula. 
  The pro-Russian chauvinists and their media, the document 
stresses, are trying to convince people that Kiev is responsible 
for all of Crimea's troubles, and that Ukraine is putting brakes 
on the development of the autonomous republic's economy. Rumors 
are constantly spread about accelerated militarization of the 
peninsula. This campaign has already reached its goal: Fear is 
common among Crimean residents and households are getting 
involved in interethnic clashes. 
  The shadow parliament, the Civic Congress of Crimea, demands 
that the Supreme Council of Crimea should be dissolved, the 
republic's presidency abolished, and direct presidential rule 
imposed here. The demands include urgent and fair settlement of 
the Black Sea Fleet problems, withdrawal of Russian ships from 
Ukraine, prevention of the lease of Ukrainian territories to 
foreign military bases, and recognition of the powers of the 
majles as a body representing the interests of the entire 
Crimean-Tatar people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

