<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Ukraine's Supreme Council Decree on the Election of First </F>
Deputy Chairman of Ukraine's Supreme Council" issued on 25 May; 
and biographical information on the newly elected first deputy 
chairman of Ukraine's Supreme Council] 
  [Text] Ukraine's Supreme Council decrees as follows: 
  To elect [as published] Oleksandr Mykolayovych Tkachenko, 
Ukraine's people's deputy, as first deputy chairman of Ukraine's 
Supreme Council. 
  O. Moroz, Chairman of Ukraine's Supreme Council 
  Kiev, 25 May 1994 
<H5>  First Deputy Chairman of Ukraine's Supreme Council Oleksandr </H5>
Mykolayovych Tkachenko 
  Oleksandr Mykolayovych Tkachenko was born on 7 March 1939 in 
the town of Shpola in Cherkasy Oblast. He advanced in his 
career from metal worker at a machine and tractor station to 
Ukraine's minister of agriculture. He was elected as secretary 
of Komsomol [Young Communist League] rayon committee, secretary 
and first secretary of the [Communist] party rayon committee, 
and chairman of the executive committee of the Ternopil Oblast 
Council of People's Deputies. He was first deputy chairman of 
the Council of Ministers of the Ukrainian SSR. Recently, he 
headed the agro-industrial association "Land and People." 
  He is a member of Ukraine's Peasant Party and Ukraine's 
people's deputy of three convocations. 
  O. Tkachenko is married. His wife is an economist. He has a 
grown-up daughter. 

</TEXT>

