<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Congressional Delegation Holds News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Congressional Delegation Holds News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105111494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0951 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 31 May (ITAR-RASS) -- [Senator] Sam Nunn and 
other U.S. senators will propose to President Bill Clinton that 
the first joint U.S-Russian military exerises within the 
framework of the peacekeeping forces should be held on the 
territory of the United States and not Russia, Sam Nunn, 
chairman of the U.S. Armed Services Committee of the Senate, 
said today at a news conference in Moscow which summed up the 
results of the working meeting between the parliamentarians of 
the United States and the Russian Federation on questions of 
defense and security. 
  The U.S. delegation was composed of seven senators -- four 
Republicans and three Democrats -- highly assessed the results 
of the meeting. "We received enthusiastically the idea of 
civilian control [kontrol] over nuclear and other types of 
weapons of mass destruction," Sam Nunn noted. He stressed that 
the United States and Russia should step up their work to reduce 
the risk of weapons of mass destruction being used. 
  The sides agreed that it is necessary to do everything to 
prevent the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction and of 
missile technology. "The United States, Russia, and other great 
powers have no interest at all in nuclear, chemical, and 
bacteriological weapons spreading around the world," Sam Nunn 
noted. 
  Sergey Yushenkov, chairman of the Committee for Defense of 
the State Duma, called the meeting between the parliamentarians 
of the two great powers a "significant event". During the 
two-day discussion, he noted, problems concerning external 
security and defense policy were discussed. The sides stressed 
that civilian control over the armed forces has great importance 
for strengthening the system of mutual security. "Joint 
Russian-American military exercises are the symbol of trust 
between the two countries," Sergey Yushenkov said. "In this 
respect, the implementation of other programs in the military 
sphere, including the Partnership for Peace program, are also of 
great importance," he said. 
  The two parliamentary defense committees agreed to continue 
the dialogue which, to all appearances, will take place on the 
territory of the United States now. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

