<H3> <TI>   Missile Forces Commander Praises Missile Retargeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Missile Forces Commander Praises Missile Retargeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005201694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1313 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Excerpts] Moscow, 30 May--Russia and the strategic 
offensive forces of the United States and Great Britain have 
taken effective step to create a higher nuclear threshold in the 
world, Lieutenant General Viktor Yesin, head of the operations 
directorate of the main staff of the Russian strategic missile 
forces, told an ITAR-TASS correspondent today. In his opinion, 
the retargeting of missiles at deserted sea areas, carried out 
under existing agreements, will not diminish the combat 
readiness of Russia's nuclear forces. [passage omitted] 
  Gen. Yesin said that all retargeting operations had been 
completed within agreed deadlines and that they guarantee, as 
envisaged in the agreements, a reduction of the nuclear danger 
worldwide. In his words, this act of goodwill and mutual trust 
does not free the strategic missile forces from the obligation 
to defend the motherland and to maintain strategic stability on 
the planet. 

</TEXT>

