  [Text] Russia and the United States have shared their 
experience in training officers for ground troops, the ground 
forces Press center reports. A U.S. military delegation led by 
General John (Fraser), deputy head of the ground troops training 
center, today completed its work in the Russian Armed Forces. 
The delegation had been staying in Moscow since 22 May in 
accordance with a treaty on contacts between Russian and U.S. 
armed forces. In the course of the visit, the Americans visited 
the Vystrel advanced training courses for officers and the Taman 
motorized rifle division. In the training classes and at the 
test grounds they familiarized themselves with the training of 
Russian officers and shared their experience in officer 
training. 

