<H3> <TI>   Deputy Condemns Obstruction of Russian Weapons Export </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Condemns Obstruction of Russian Weapons Export </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105212494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1919 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fair play with Russia in the world weapons market 
would not hurt U.S. strategic interests, Sergey Yushenkov, 
chairman of the State Duma Defense Committee said today. 
  He told INTERFAX that Washington's obstruction of Russian 
weapon export, as in the case of the failed sales of MiG-29 
fighter planes to Venezuela, forced Russia to deal with 
undesirable partners. 
  As a result, Yushenkov said, odious dictatorial regimes 
obtained weapons through third or fourth countries and created 
tension for the entire world community. 

</TEXT>

