<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Ends Visit to Brussels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Ends Visit to Brussels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805143594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1401 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2805143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 28 TASS -- Russian Defence Minister Pavel 
Grachev returned to Moscow on Saturday from Belgium where he was 
on an official visit. During the visit Grachev addressed 
NATO leaders in Brussels to present them with Russia's concept 
of partnership with the West and its new military doctrine and 
held talks with NATO officials. 
  On the way back to Russia Grachev made a stopover in 
Wuensdorf where the Western group of Russian troops is stationed 
to discuss the withdrawal of troops due to be completed this 
August. 

</TEXT>

