<H3> <TI>   Churkin Says Jun `Major' Month for Bosnia Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin Says Jun `Major' Month for Bosnia Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105211594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2052 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105211594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Naryshkin] </F>
  [Text] Zagreb June 1 TASS -- Moscow thinks that June should 
become the "major" month in the achievement of Bosnian peace 
settlement and, possibly, the solution of the whole set of 
Yugoslav problems, special representative of the Russian 
president Vitaliy Churkin told an exclusive ITAR-TASS interview 
here on Tuesday. 
  "We plan and, I think, will soon work on a possibility of 
another meeting of foreign ministers. There is common 
understanding that this meeting should be held at the Russian 
representation in Geneva," he said. 
  "State leaders are interested in the initiative of President 
Boris Yeltsin to hold a special summit on Bosnian settlement. 
If this summit is not held till mid-June, the Yugoslav problems 
will be discussed at the Naples meeting of the G7 to be for the 
first time held as a meeting of the `political eight' with 
fully-fledged Russian participation in political discussions. 
This is an opportunity that cannot be missed," said Churkin. 

</TEXT>

