<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   India to Receive Military Spares From Russia, Ukraine </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    India to Receive Military Spares From Russia, Ukraine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106101594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0916 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Leonid Kotov] </F>
  [Text] New Delhi June 1 TASS -- The Indian armed forces 
will receive a large consignment of much needed spare parts for 
its military equipment within the next three months, Indian 
Minister of State for Defence M. Mallikarjun said here at a 
conference of the Indian naval officers. 
  Supplies will be realized in accordance with contracts 
signed 
during the visits last month by the Indian military delegation 
to Russia and Ukraine. The minister emphasised that shortages 
of spare parts creates serious problems in maintaining high 
level combat readiness of all kinds of armed forces of India. 
They are crucial for the air force, which is equipped with 
"MiG-29" fighters, and tank troops, mainly armed with "T-72" 
tanks. 
  At the same time, Mallikarjun recalled that the spare part 
problem for the armed forces might be eventually resolved only 
by increasing their production in Indian defence enterprises. 
The Indian Government has decided to earmark 230 billion rupees 
for its requirements this year. A considerable part of this 
money will be used to produce military equipment and spare parts 
for it at state enterprises of the country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

