<H3> <TI>   Delegation Arrives in Venezuela </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Arrives in Venezuela </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105093194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0817 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Dmitriyev] </F>
  [Text] Caracas May 31 TASS -- Venezuela is known as "South- 
American Kuwait", it is a leading oil power in the Western 
Hemisphere. 
  A delegation of Russian lawmakers arrived here on Monday [30 
May]. Vladimir Shumeyko, chairman of the Federation Council, is 
at the head of the delegation. 
  The delegation is making a tour of several Latin-American 
countries. It has already visited Chili, Argentina and Brazil. 
  When answering to journalists' questions at the airport, 
Shumeyko emphasized the necessity "to go ahead with developing 
Russo- Venezuelian relations as fast as we can". 
  The programme for the visit includes a meeting between 
Shumeyko and President Rafael Caldera Rodriguez of Venezuela, 
during which the former is to hand in a personal message on the 
part of Russian President Boris Yeltsin. 
  The delegation is also to meet with leaders of Venezuelian 
parliament, Foreign Minister Miguel Angel Burelli. 
  Shumeyko is to address a plenary session of the council of 
the National Congress of Venezuela. 
  The Russian lawmakers will also meet with Caracas Mayor 
Asdrubal Agiar. 

</TEXT>

