<H3> <TI>   State Duma Chairman Receives Greek Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Chairman Receives Greek Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105215194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1503 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 31 May -- "For Russia the Balkans are not 
just a dot on the map, but it has a place in our hearts", Ivan 
Rybkin, the chairman of the State Duma, stated during today's 
meeting with Karolos Papoulias, the foreign minister of the 
Greek republic. "We want very much", the speaker of the lower 
chamber of the Russian parliament noted also, "that there should 
be no hot spots in Europe and even more so that the flame of war 
should not burn in the fraternal Yugoslavia". 
  Karolos Papoulias assured Ivan Rybkin that on international 
issues the positions of Russia and Greece are similar or fully 
coincide and noted that his side is interested in "Russia again 
taking a worthy place in the Balkans, which it used to occupy 
earlier and which it is worthy of by right". Incidentally, he 
admitted that "the European Union countries have committed 
mistakes with regard to Yugoslavia and Greece bears 
responsibility for it as well". At the same time Karolos 
Papoulias stressed that "despite the fact that no-one likes 
this, Greece will follow the same path as Russia in the matter 
of a peaceful settlement in the Balkans". 
  The sides also discussed issues of interparliamentary 
cooperation between the two countries and spoke about the need 
to expand them. 

</TEXT>

