<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Nuclear Test Site To Be Handed Over to Kazakhstan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106091494 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 1 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia is ready to hand over the nuclear test range 
near Kurchatov to Kazakhstan as of 1 June. The Kurchatov test 
range was used for nuclear tests from 1949 until 1991, when the 
moratorium on nuclear arms tests was introduced. 
  Kazakhstan proposes to turn Kurchatov into an international 
center for radiological, engineering, and medical research. 

</TEXT>

