<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contraband Raw Materials Seized on Latvia, Estonia Borders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Contraband Raw Materials Seized on Latvia, Estonia Borders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM3105153694 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 31 May 94 p 
4 </F>

<F P=103> PM3105153694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified news agency: "Border Barrier Saves </F>
Raw Materials"] 
  [Text] Operation "Barrier" -- aimed at putting a stop to 
smuggling and other illegal activity -- was conducted 16 through 
20 May on the border with Estonia and Latvia by units from the 
Northwest Border District in conjunction with Belorussian 
[Belarusian] border guards. As a result, contraband worth 905 
million rubles [R] -- including 56 tonnes of steel and 25 tonnes 
of titanium alloys -- was seized in the course of the five days. 
In total in 1993 the troops of the Northwest Border District 
seized contraband worth R4.3 billion, and the figure since the 
start of 1994 is R2 billion. The export of around 2,000 tonnes 
of nonferrous metals and 600 tonnes of fuels and lubricants has 
been prevented. 

</TEXT>

