<H3> <TI>   State Duma Said Monitoring Crimean Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Said Monitoring Crimean Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305102994 Moscow RIA in English 0901 GMT 23 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2305102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 23, RIA -- "Members of the Russian 
parliament are monitoring the situation around the Crimea," said 
Vladimir Lukin, chairman of the State Duma Committee on 
International Affairs. "I believe that the State Duma should 
support the statement of President Yeltsin to the effect that 
the use of force, in any form, to settle the conflict is 
inadmissible." 
  He said he was afraid that the forthcoming presidential 
elections in Ukraine could negatively affect the situation in 
the Crimea, as presidential candidates might attempt to play the 
Crimean card to prove their patriotism. It would be best to 
freeze the situation until the elections, and to encourage Kiev 
and Simferopol to hold talks and refrain from "war-mongering." 

</TEXT>

