<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Mineyev] </F>
  [Excerpts] Brussels, 31 May -- [passage omitted] Having 
arrived in Brussels on Tuesday morning [Kyrgyz President] Akayev 
visited the European Commission twice, where he had talks with 
its heads -- Hans van der Broek and Leon Brittan. At the end of 
these meetings a partnership and cooperation agreement between 
the European Union [EU] and Kyrgyzstan was initialled. 
