<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baku Claims Armenians Invade Nakhichevan Enclave </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baku Claims Armenians Invade Nakhichevan Enclave </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105124094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1102 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following preliminary artillery [fire], 500-strong 
Armenian divisions, backed by armored vehicles, invaded 
Azerbaijan's Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic last Monday. 
  The Azerbaijani Defense Ministry told INTERFAX that the 
Armenians launched an attack on the village of Gyuinnet in 
Nakhichevan's Sadarak region, killing four Azerbaijani 
servicemen, wounding two and taking three hostage. 
  Baku says that Armenian formations advanced about 5 
kilometers into Nakhichevan, consolidating their positions on 
the occupied heights. 
  INTERFAX has not yet obtained any information from the 
Armenian Defense Ministry. 

</TEXT>

