<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Colonels Detained for Participation in Assassinations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colonels Detained for Participation in Assassinations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106123394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1012 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A total of five high-ranking officials of the 
Georgian power ministries were detained in May. They are 
suspected of participating in the assassination of defense 
minister Nikoloz Kekelidze and deputy defense minister and chief 
of transport police Giya Gulua. Reliable sources told Interfax 
that all the detained are colonels. 
  Kekelidze was killed as a result of an explosion on February 
3 morning in his house in Tbilisi. Gulua had been killed near 
his house in Tbilisi on April 20 morning. 
  During the recent six months about ten terrorist acts 
against 
high-ranking officers of the Defense Ministry, the Interior 
Ministry and the Mkhedrioni armed group have been carried out in 
Georgia. Chief of the Mkhedrioni Rustav regional department 
Temur Talakhadze was killed in January, a Security Ministry 
officer Vasil Koberidze in February. None of the murderers has 
been found. 

</TEXT>

