<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Addresses Parliament on Crimean Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Addresses Parliament on Crimean Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106111794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1012 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and Mikhail </F>
Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev, 1ST Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- "The Ukrainian Supreme 
Council should adopt decisions that would be proportionate to 
the current situation in relations between Ukraine and the 
Republic of Crimea", Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk said 
today in an address to the Ukrainian parliament. 
  In his view, "the political forces that have proclaimed the 
secession of the Republic of Crimea from Ukraine and its merger 
with the Russian Federation have now gained power in the 
autonomous republic." He believes that the Crimean leaders have 
chosen two routes. The first is the adoption of a constitution 
that proposes to proclaim the Crimean autonomy an independent 
state, and the second is to restore the old Soviet Union, which 
is impracticable. He believes that the conclusion should be 
unambiguous: The Crimean issue ought to be solved only in the 
framework of the Ukrainian Constitution, the president stressed. 
"We must do it," Leonid Kravchuk said. 
  He made the proposal to immediately form the Ukrainian 
Constitutional Court, which should repeal all decisions of the 
Crimean parliament and president contradicting the laws of the 
Ukrainian state. He also proposed making amendments and 
addendums to the Ukrainian Constitution, to the law on 
demarcation of powers between the Ukraine and the Republic of 
the Crimea, in which it is to be clearly defined that the 
Crimean autonomous entity is the territory of the Ukrainian 
state. In the opinion of the president of Ukraine, all power 
ministries of the Crimea should also be subordinated to Kiev. 
It is also important to settle budgetary relations. "Now we 
must take the most radical measures to stabilize the situation, 
because the consequences could be even worse," Leonid Kravchuk 
stressed. And this needs to be done in the framework of the 
Constitution, be believes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38651 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov105_h_94002" </HT>


