<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Terms Dushanbe Assassination `Vile' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Terms Dushanbe Assassination `Vile' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105222194 Moscow RIA in English 1935 GMT 31 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3105222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 31, RIA -- The assassination of 
Lieutenant-Colonel Vladimir Borisenkov, a senior staff member of 
Russian frontier troops in Tajikistan, has been described as 
"vile and filthy" by the Russian Foreign Ministry. 
  Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman Grigoriy Karasin, who 
read 
out the document at a news briefing for journalists, noted that 
this was not the first act of terrorism against Russian 
servicemen. 
  "These acts are planned and executed," said the diplomat, 
"by 
those who are not interested in defusing the situation in 
Tajikistan and who want to drive a wedge in Russian-Tajik 
relations". 
  The statement points to the need for the Tajik authorities 
thoroughly to investigate the murder, and catch and punish the 
perpetrators. The Foreign Ministry expressed condolences to 
Borisenkov's relatives. 
  Russian diplomatic sources told RIA that within minutes of 
the act becoming known, Emomali Rakhmonov, the Tajik head of 
state, phoned to the Russian frontier troop headquarters and 
said all measures would be taken to catch the criminals and 
asked to convey condolences to the family of the killed man. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

