<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Addresses Moscow Meeting With U.S. Senators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Addresses Moscow Meeting With U.S. Senators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105145194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1200 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report over video by correspondent A. Peslyak; from the </F>
"Vesti" newscast] 
  [Text] [Sergey] Yushenkov, [chairman of State Duma 
Committee for Defense], said that comparison of the systems of 
civilian control over the armed forces in the two countries 
[United States and Russia] shows that our system is not 
developed. 
  Russian Foreign Minister [Andrey Kozyrev] said that it is 
not 
democratic to lay down the condition that Russia should 
unilaterally accept the obligation to end arms supplies to 
certain regions in the country before talks can start. We are 
for stability without conditions being laid down for one side. 
The Karabakh conflict, which has destabilized the situation in 
the Caucasus, creates problems for us on our southern border, 
yet some people abroad see us as neo-imperialists here, rather 
than as peacekeepers, and even regard Russia's efforts as being 
opposed to those of the CSCE. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

