<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Postpones Decision on Baltic Peacekeeping Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Postpones Decision on Baltic Peacekeeping Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0106125794 Tallinn BNS in English 1025 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0106125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, 31 May, BNS -- The Estonian Cabinet at its 
meeting Tuesday [31 May] ruled to postpone its formal decision 
on setting up the Estonian company under the joint Baltic 
peacekeeping battalion plan and refer the draft decision for 
further review to the Defense Ministry. 
  Under the joint Baltic plan, Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania 
would each set up a company as part of the Baltic battalion to 
be formed for participation in U.N. peacekeeping operations. 
  All three countries also count on Western support for the 
project. "International assistance programs are expected to be 
launched as soon as we have a legal basis for the formation of 
the peacekeeping company," Enn Tupp, the head of the defense 
policy department in the Estonian Defense Ministry said in an 
interview earlier. 
  He said the three countries hope to staff the battalion by 
August. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

