<H3> <TI>   Foreign Affairs Minister Gives News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Affairs Minister Gives News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106154894 Yerevan SNARK in English 1118 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 31 May 31 (SNARK) -- "There prepared 33 
agreements in previous seven rounds of the Russian-Georgian 
negotiations," said to the journalists at his today's press 
conference the Georgian Foreign Affairs Minister Aleksandr 
Chikvaidze. 
  "Practically, we created the legislative basis for 
development of the relations between two states." 
  Aleksandr Chikvaidze denied the reports, some mass media 
spread, on the fact that there, at the negotiations, were 
determined the terms of the Russian troops' existence on the 
territory of Georgia -- 50 years. Aleksandr Chikvaidze said, 
"no terms were discussed at the negotiations." 
  Speaking on the Russian military bases creation on the 
territory of Georgia, Mr. Chikvaidze said, "If only Georgia 
offers her territory for Russian military bases, she should get 
something in exchange. This question couldn't be solved without 
referendum, without Parliament's content. Yet some more rounds 
of negotiations are being expected." The eighth round of 
negotiations is expected by the end of June. 

</TEXT>

