<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denial of Report on Failure of Meeting on Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denial of Report on Failure of Meeting on Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106185994 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1512 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We are presenting information supplied by CS agency 
[as heard]. 
  A CS information agency correspondent has been told by 
Deputy 
Security Minister Avtandil Ioseliani that a report broadcast in 
an Alioni TV program alleging that quadripartite talks in Sochi 
have failed does not correspond to the facts. 
  A meeting of the quadripartite commission on Abkhazia took 
place in Sochi on 29 and 30 May. The meeting had to create a 
foundation for the return of forcefully displaced people to 
Abkhazia. During the meeting, the Abkhaz side demanded that a 
paragraph be included in an application form according to which 
Georgian refugees would promise to abide by Abkhazian laws. The 
Georgian and Russian parties at the meeting unequivocally 
rejected the demand because it was absurd to have a formulation 
like this before an Abkhazian status had been established. 
  The meeting discussed an issue of registering refugees and 
possibilities of information exchange in this connection. A 
joint statement has been adopted. 
  According to Mr. Avtandil Ioseliani, the next meeting of the 
quadripartite commission is to be held in Sochi on 20-21 June. 

</TEXT>

