  [Text] Tbilisi, 31 May (SNARK) -- Today Georgian Parliament 
accepted a decision to create a special commission to struggle 
against the mafia. The decision is the result of the discussion 
the deputies were taking round the worsening criminal situation 
existing in Georgia. 
  Irina Sarishvili, one of the leaders of the 
National-Democratic Party, said at today's session, "no doubt, 
mafia is heading Georgian state." 

</TEXT>

