  [Text] Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan signed a 
decree today to form an Armenian Republic state delegation to 
hold talks with the Russian Federation. It established an 
Armenian Republic state delegation to formulate a system of 
legal foundation for bilateral relations between the Armenian 
Republic and the Russian Federation, to resolve emerging 
practical problems, and to coordinate the talks held with Russia 
through various departments. The Armenian State Minister Armenak 
Gazaryan has been appointed the head of the delegation. 

