<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Centrists Prepare for Conference on New Intra-CIS Union </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Centrists Prepare for Conference on New Intra-CIS Union </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0106130094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 1 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> MK0106130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Viktor Yadukha report: "Conference of Centrists To Be Held </F>
in Crimea"] 
  [Text] Preparations are under way in Sevastopol for a 
conference of centrist political forces of Russia, Ukraine, and 
Belorussia [Belarus] with Kazakhstan and Moldavia [Moldova] 
showing interest in it. According to Yuriy Komov, one of the 
conference organizers and spokesman for the Crimean Party of 
Social Guarantees, the conference is supposed to raise the 
question of a new union within the CIS framework. 
  Taking part in the preparations on behalf on Ukraine is the 
Interregional Kuchma-Grinev Bloc of Reforms, and the Civil 
Congress of Ukraine. Representing Russia are the Party of 
Russian Unity and Accord and the Russian Movement for Democratic 
Reforms. Also invited were Social Democrats and Populists. 
"The threat of a conflict in Crimea may bring to naught 
centrists' unification efforts," Yuriy Komov stated. "Our plan 
is to get all the documents signed at the Livadia Palace on the 
50th anniversary of the Yalta Conference." 

</TEXT>

