<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia, ROK Agree To Establish Trade Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia, ROK Agree To Establish Trade Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206095494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0911 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 2 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and Russia 
will soon establish a trade committee to discuss ways to promote 
and strengthen bilateral cooperation in the fields of trade, 
investment and technology. 
  The committee's creation was agreed in Moscow on Thursday 
when the two nations' trade ministers signed a memorandum to 
that effect. Attending the meeting were Korean Trade, Industry 
and Energy Minister Kim Chol-su and Russian Foreign Economic 
Relations Minister Oleg Davydov. Kim Chol-su is accompanying 
President Kim Yong-sam on his state visit to Russia. 
  The ministers agreed to hold the committee's first meeting 
in 
Seoul this year to be headed by the two sides' assistant 
ministers. 
  During the meeting, Russia promised to continue offering 
preferential tariffs for Korean goods that are half the most- 
favored-nation rate. In addition, Moscow said it will dispatch 
an evaluation team to Korea to designate six more 
safety-certifying agents for easier customs clearance of Korean 
goods bound to be shipped to Russia. 
  They also agreed to set up a working-level committee to 
support construction of a Korea-Russia Trade Center at a site 
owned by Moscow University Campus. 
  Minister Kim pointed out that there is still 755 million 
U.S. 
dollars receivable from Russia for Korean exports, saying this 
uncollected money resulted from a foreign currency freeze in 
December 1990 imposed by the former Soviet Union's External 
Economic Bank. 
  With regard to Minister Kim's call for early settlement of 
Russia's outstanding receivables, Davydov proposed a meeting in 
Moscow to discuss terms of payment and creditor-confirmation 
procedures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

