Sevryukov] 
  [Text] Moscow June 1 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin may visit the Greek island of Corfu (Kerkyra) in June to 
take part in the ceremony of signing an agreement between Russia 
and the European Union [EU], Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev said on Wednesday. 
  The announcement was made after his talks with Greek Foreign 
Minister Karolos Papoulias who is in Moscow on a three-day 
official visit. 
  Relations between Russia and the EU featured prominently at 
the talks, Kozyrev said. He recalled that at present Greece 
holds presidency in the European Union and praised its support 
and assistance in the development of the agreement. 
  "I think that the history of this cooperation will continue 
and important events may take place before Greece hands over its 
presidency," he said. Kozyrev made it clear that the work on 
the agreement may be completed before June 24 when the EU 
leaders gather for their meeting in Corfu. 

