<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arrangements Made for Paying Debts to UN Bodies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arrangements Made for Paying Debts to UN Bodies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105205994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1835 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During the second quarter of 1994 Russia will pay 90 
million dollars in order to cover a part of its debt to the 
budgets of the UN system organizations. The appropriate 
resolution was signed by Russian Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin. 
  During the third and the fourth quarters of 1994 Russia will 
pay 169 million dollars to the UN budget as membership dues. 
  Russia will also pay 14 million dollars to the UNESCO budget 
and 11 million dollars to the International Atomic Energy 
Agency. In accordance with the government resolution, during 
the third and the fourth quarter of 1994 the Russian Finance 
Ministry will allot 200 million dollars to pay its membership 
dues to the international organizations. 
  "The appropriate funds in foreign currency must be allotted 
from the resources which the federal budget has planned to use 
for non-trade operations," the resolution underlined. 

</TEXT>

