<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Denies Chernomyrdin To Visit Tbilisi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Denies Chernomyrdin To Visit Tbilisi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106141094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1349 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 1 TASS -- A Russian Government press 
service official denied mass media reports on Wednesday that 
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin will visit Tbilisi 
during his vacation. 
  The official said that Chernomyrdin may visit Novorossiyisk 
where a new Russian port is being built, but most likely in the 
second half of his vacation. 
  The Russian prime minister is now vacationing on the Black 
Sea. His spokesman Valeriy Grishin said earlier today that 
during the vacation Chernomyrdin will continue working on the 
second package of economic decrees which is now being drawn up 
by the government. 
  The spokesman said that until the last minute it was not 
clear whether or not Chernomyrdin will take his leave now, 
mainly because of his active involvement in the work on the 
package of economic decrees aimed at continuing economic reforms 
in Russia. The first package was recently signed by President 
Boris Yeltsin. 
  Grishin denied reports that Chernomyrdin would work on his 
book during his vacation. "There will be simply no time left for 
that. Besides, he needs rest too," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

