<H3> <TI>   Deputy Premier Receives Kuwaiti Parliament Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Premier Receives Kuwaiti Parliament Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106133094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1128 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 1 TASS -- "Kuwait is prepared to change 
its legislation and adopt new laws if necessary to promote the 
development of larger-scale and long-term cooperation with 
Russia", Ahmad 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Sa'dun, speaker of the Kuwaiti 
National Assembly, who leads a parliamentary delegation, told 
Russian First Vice-Premier Oleg Soskovets here on Wednesday. 
Mr. Sa'dun expressed gratitude to the Russian Federation for 
its support to Kuwait in upholding its independence. 
  Soskovets, having expressed appreciation of Kuwait's desire 
to strengthen its defence capacity, emphasised that high 
technologies in the Russian military industry would help resolve 
many a matter concerning Russian-Kuwaiti cooperation in this 
respect. 
  "But it is up to your parliament to decide on whether to 
endorse or turn down funds necessary for the purchase of this 
technology which we could sell to you", Soskovets added. 
  Russia would welcome Kuwaiti investments in various branches 
of the Russian economy to promote economic reform, Soskovets 
pointed out. 

</TEXT>

