<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary Views Chernomyrdin Visit to China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commentary Views Chernomyrdin Visit to China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0106193794 Moscow Radio Moscow in Mandarin 1000 GMT 31 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0106193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Brief commentary" by station commentator Mulatov from the </F>
"Half an Hour With Wang Xiao" program] 
  [Text] The seven agreements between Russia and China 
signed during the Russian delegation's visit will strengthen and 
continue the equal and mutually beneficial cooperation achieved 
over the last few years in economics, trade, science and 
technology, and other fields. Setting their sights on the 
future [words indistinct] the two countries have decided to 
raise the neighborly and friendly relations between them to a 
new level of development -- says a report on the outcome of 
[words indistinct] visit to China. The document, which sums up 
the outcome of the visit, also says the two countries will take 
full advantage of their geographical closeness and make full use 
of the complementariness between the two countries' economies. 
Both Moscow and Beijing understand that the neighborly and 
friendly relations and the mutually beneficial cooperation 
between them are in line with the fundamental interests of the 
two countries and their peoples and are an important factor for 
preserving peace and stability and for ensuring development in 
the Asia-Pacific region as well as in the whole world. We also 
like to point out that the Russian delegation's visit to China 
was widely reported in detail by the media of Eastern and 
Western countires. At the beginning, some Western media doubted 
that Russia might have an intention to develop bilateral 
military technology cooperation with China. Such cooperation 
will be developed under the condition that the two countries 
fulfill their international obligations -- this should not cause 
anyone to be suspicions. 
  During the talks, the two sides stressed the importance of 
reaching an agreement on taking measures as soon as possible to 
reduce their troops and armament and military trainings in 
disputed areas. They believed this will not only enhance mutual 
trust and understanding between the two countries, but also will 
contribute to preserving peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific 
region. 
  During their talks, Chernomyrdin and Li Peng also discussed 
international issues of common interest. The two countries' 
identical and similar stands on some major international issues 
were confirmed. This will be the foundation for the two 
countries to strengthen their constructive cooperation in 
regional and world affairs. 
  In short, the dialogue between the two governments has 
yielded good results. Currently, the two sides are preparing 
for Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to Russia. The two 
countries believe that positive dialogues at all levels, 
including the highest level, are prerequisites for promoting 
neighborly and friendly relations and mutually beneficial 
cooperation between them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

