<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Favors Referendum on Territorial Set-Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Favors Referendum on Territorial Set-Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106121694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1012 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Liberal-Democratic Party leader Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy told representatives of the Islamic Cultural Center 
that after coming to power, his party would hold a referendum on 
dividing Russia into guberniyas (provinces), the 
Liberal-Democratic Party's Press Secretary Grigoriy 
Serebrennikov told INTERFAX. 
  Zhirinovskiy believes that the current national-territorial 
division of Russia breeds conflicts. 
  Asked about his attitude to the Muslims, Zhirinovskiy said 
that the Liberal-Democratic Party was a secular party and that 
it was tolerant of all religions. He also noted that Tatar 
Akhmet Khalitov was his party's vice-chairman. 
  Serebrennikov stated that the meeting was attended by 
religious and public figures from Azerbaijan, Tatarstan and 
Dagestan. 

</TEXT>

