<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Advance Payments Needed for Russian Gas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Advance Payments Needed for Russian Gas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106200894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1857 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Chisinau 1 June TASS -- Russia said on Wednesday [1 
June] that from now on it will supply gas to Moldavia [Moldova] 
only on the basis of advance payments. 
  The decision announced by Russia's gas supplying concern 
Gazprom followed Moldavia's failure to pay for earlier gas 
supplies. 
  Moldavian gas industry head Boris Karandyuk said that 
Moldavia's debt to Russia is estimated at 257 billion roubles. 
About 107 billion roubles of that sum is owed by the break-away 
Dniester republic which is seeking economic and political 
independence from Moldavia. 
  About 70 per cent of the debt belongs to the Moldovenergo 
Association which supplies the republic with electricity and 
heat. 
  Karandyuk said that Moldavia has so far paid only 40 billion 
roubles and is ready to send a large shipment of food and 
industrial products worth 16 billion roubles to pay part of the 
remaining sum. 
  "We are seeking ways to pay the debt and intend to resort to 
foreign credits," Karandyuk said. 

</TEXT>

