<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Receives U.S. Senators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Receives U.S. Senators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106170994 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Foreign Minister Kanat Saudabayev received 
U.S. Senators Arlen Specter and Robert Bennett who are currently 
on a visit to Almaty. They exchanged opinions on Kazakh-U.S. 
political, trade, and economic relations. The U.S. side, in 
particular, expressed interest in progress of privatization in 
the republic and its peculiarities as well as problems related 
to it. Kanat Saudabayev told the guests about the 
denationalization of state industrial enterprises which is in 
progress. He said that the biggest U.S. investments are being 
made in the Almaty tobacco factory and the Shymkent 
confectionery factory. The minister stressed that this 
testifies to the fact that the republic has serious intentions 
for the market economy. 
  They also touched upon the multifaceted relations with 
Kazakhstan's closest neighbor, Russia, and Kazakhstan's 
cooperation with it. The senators handed Kanat Saudabayev a 
personal letter from U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher 
congratulating Saudabayev on his appointment as foreign minister. 

</TEXT>

