<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Cooperation Agreement Signed With Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Cooperation Agreement Signed With Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106171294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kazakhstan and Turkey concluded an agreement in 
Ankara on cooperation in the field of recovery, refining, 
haulage and selling of Kazakh oil. [passage omitted] In line 
with the agreement, a joint Kazakh-Turkish company will begin 
work in August-September this year at a deposit in the west of 
the republic. [passage omitted] 
  Speaking at the ceremony of signing the agreement, Syzdyk 
Abishev said that the government of Kazakhstan understands 
Ankara's anxiety regarding the transportation of oil via the 
Black Sea. He expressed confidence that this problem can be 
tackled if the interested parties are involved. Abishev 
stressed that Kazakhstan and Turkey have concluded about 60 
agreements, and most of them are at the stage of implementation. 
Over 150 Turkish companies are working in the republic now, and 
several joint banks have been set up. Turkey granted Kazakhstan 
a loan worth $200 million. This money is used for construction 
of a five-star hotel, a textile factory, a tannery, and other 
projects. 

</TEXT>

