<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Rules for Entering Yakut Republic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Rules for Entering Yakut Republic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106174694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1336 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The President of Yakutia Mikhail Nikolayev has set 
special rules for entry and presence in the East Siberian 
republic within the Russian Federation. 
  The terms for entry and stay he decreed concern nationals 
from CIS and other countries as well as citizens of Russia's 
republics, not signatories to the Federative Treaty. 
  From now they will require a special invitation, agreed with 
local authorities, to be allowed into Yakutia. Besides, 
foreigners must identify their planned whereabouts, including 
the name of the street and house number, explain the purpose of 
their arrival and the duration of their stay in the republic. 
  In some instances, an applicant may be forbidden entry or be 
deported before his or her term of stay is up. Reasons for this 
could be actions detrimental to national security, public order, 
the established traditions and moral standards, custom, 
currency, and other regulations of Russia and Yakutia. 

</TEXT>

