<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Price, Wage Increases Take Effect 1 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Price, Wage Increases Take Effect 1 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106124094 Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN in Russian 1002 GMT 31 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- In accordance with a 
resolution of the Government of Uzbekistan, from tomorrow the 
price of gasoline will rise from 600 to 1,000 sum-coupons a 
liter, electricity for residential premises from 10 to 15 
sum-coupons a kW hour. The cost of travel on urban 
transportation will double -- for a journey by bus, trolleycar, 
tramcar, and metro will be 100 sum- coupons. The price of 
tin-baked bread is set at 400 sum-coupons compared with the 
present 105. 
  At the same time, from 1 June the minimum wage will be 
increased by 50 percent, bringing it up to 75,000 sum-coupons. 

</TEXT>

